🔁 Recursion – Generate All Binary Strings
link: https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/generate-all-binary-strings/1
Given a number n, print all binary strings of length n.
✅ Tags: Recursion, Backtracking, Binary, String Generation, Easy
❓ What is the base case?
❓ How to form the recursive calls?

👨‍💻 Intuition:
At every index, you have two choices: put 0 or put 1.
Recursively build the string character by character.
📌 Base Case:
If n == 0, print the string and return.
🔁 Recursive Steps:
cpp
CopyEdit
void generateBinaryStrings(int n, string current) {
    if (n == 0) {
        cout << current << endl;
        return;
    }

    // Choice 1: Add '0'
    generateBinaryStrings(n - 1, current + "0");

    // Choice 2: Add '1'
    generateBinaryStrings(n - 1, current + "1");
}
📞 Initial Call:
generateBinaryStrings(n, "")
📌 Example:
Input: n = 2
Output:
CopyEdit
00  
01  
10  
11
🕒 Time Complexity: O(2^n)
📦 Space Complexity: O(n) (for recursion stack)
